fields.description:
We spent just over a week climbing in the Leavenworth, Washington area, most of it bouldering.  Leavenworth is a pretty awesome bouldering destination, with a high percentage of excellent problems.

The town itself is also quite interesting, themed in a Bavarian style.  As we were there towards the end of September, Oktoberfest celebrations were just getting into full swing.

Problems included are:
The Break V2
420 Slab V0
Sunny and Steep V2
The Real Thing V4
The Pocket V4
Drugstore Cowboy V3

fields.name: Bolder Bouldering
fields.author: WWU-Digital Media in Journalism
fields.embed: <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/293145811?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0&badge=0&autopause=0&player_id=0&app_id=137790" width="1310" height="720" frameborder="0" title="Bolder Bouldering" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>
fields.description:
In a day and age when more and more rock climbers are focusing on the competition and athleticism of indoor climbing gyms, Owen Massey seeks solitude and aesthetic movement among the granite boulders of Washington state.

Western student and Leavenworth, Washington, local, Massey speaks to the philosophy and motivation behind his pursuit of bouldering, an un-roped form of rock climbing emphasizing difficulty of movement close to the ground. 

This video was shot and edited by Western visual journalism student Matthew Tangeman for the spring 2018 digital media course.
